definitions: constituting number one billion in a sequence; 1,000,000,000th

examples.text: the birth of India's billionth citizen

shortDefinitions: constituting number one billion in sequence

definitions: constituting an unspecified but very large number in a sequence

examples.text: I was late again for the billionth time

definitions: each of one billion equal parts into which something is or may be divided

examples.text: particles so small they're measured in billionths of a meter

shortDefinitions: each of one billion equal parts into which something is divided
